Child Restraint Safety Resources (alternative search terms - car seat crash tests)

Websites with independent testing data:
Consumer Reports (independent methodology): https://www.consumerreports.org/cro/car-seats.htm
Wirecutter (side-impact method; not updated since 2018): https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/reviews/best-convertible-car-seats/
BabyGearLab (NHTSA methodology): https://www.babygearlab.com/topics/vehicle-safety/best-convertible-car-seat


NHTSA:
Available test data (Component test database -> FMVSS 213 CHILD RESTRAINT SYSTEMS): https://www.nhtsa.gov/research-data/databases-and-software
Reports (not updated since 2010): https://www.nhtsa.gov/research-data/child-seat-research#notices-child-restraint-systems-federal-register-10816
Recent Report (2015): https://www.nhtsa.gov/sites/nhtsa.dot.gov/files/812116-harnessedchildrestraint.pdf
Ease of Use (completely useless): https://one.nhtsa.gov/nhtsa_eou/info.jsp?type=all

